Android is proving diferent layouts like
1. Linear Layout :
- Linear Layout is a viewgroup which is arrange all the child elements in a single direction that is Vertically or Horizontally.
- We can specify layout direction by using android:orientation attribute

2. Relative Layout :
- It is a viewgroup which displays the child elements in related postition. The position of each view can be specifies as relative to sibling 
  elements such as left or below or right or above
- It is a most flexible layout to arrange elements
